result.formatted_address: 38 Wang Chiu Rd, Kowloon Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Madison's

reviews.text:
Ordered the portobello burger medium and it was delicious. Buns are just the right amount of crisp, patty was juicy and cooked just right.
Chips can be a little more seasoned. 
Price is a little high for a burger meal but overall would come back.

Nice place and good food. If you are looking for draft beer there are over 20 on the menu but only 3 was available on a Friday night as I was told by my friend.  Food quality was good and pretty quiet place.

Went for the weekend brunch, ordered the Egg’s Benedict and Beer Battered Fish and Chips. The Egg’s Benedict came first, with 2 poached eggs, but one of the poached eggs the yolk was still raw, even the thin layer of white around the yolk was still clear (raw). Poached eggs arent the easiest to make so, no worries, I send it back. What warrants the rating of 1 star is that the manager came back to the table and try to tell me that’s how poached eggs are supposed to be. So I explained to her how poached eggs are supposed to look and the dangers of eating raw eggs. She then begrudgingly took the dish back to be remade. The second dish came out properly made. Overall the food quality is average at best, but the attitude and service from the manager was appalling. Prime example of a restaurant trying too hard to be something they can never achieve due to the lack of heart and care. Would not come back.
You must try the goods and food.
Nice beer

reviews.text: 質素不錯，服務都有禮貌。咖啡Lavazza出色。意粉份量夠，但味道稍淡。
食物質素非常高。叫了2打生豪，鵝肝多士和牛漢堡，炸魚柳薯條等。尤其生豪比酒店的還新鮮;鵝肝甘香配搭多士非常匹配。和牛漢堡要用刀叉才食到。
